<div1 type="letter">

<opener><address><addrLine>45 East Main St.,</addrLine>
<addrLine>Wallingford, CT. </addrLine>
</address>
<dateline>Aug - 2nd - '60 </dateline>
<salute>My dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute></opener>
<p>Greetings from a Conn. yankee. poet newly admitted to membership in
Mo. Chaparrals.</p>
<p>Our regent sent me the bulletin which had your name among others, and the 
suggestion that greetings might be exchanged.</p>
<p>So as a passport to friendship and as proof that I write (after my own fashion) 
I enclose a clipping -</p>
<p>In fifteen years or longer I have been a member of the Meriden (Conn) Poetry 
Society, which is a rather small organization and not as active as one might wish 
it was through an ad in Candor - that I joined Chaparrals. It seems to offer 
interesting contacts. I am hoping to correspond with many poets.</p>
<p>I note that you are Poet Laureate for which I offer congratulations.</p>

<closer>
<salute>With Kindest regards </salute>
<signed>Marion Rhodes Williams </signed>
(Mrs. Robert C. Williams, Sr)</closer>

</div1>

